{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2022-1498","published":"2022-01-22T11:03:28Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:17:38.627935Z","upstream":["CVE-2021-41039"],"summary":"mosquitto security update","details":"Mosquitto is an open source message broker that implements the MQ Telemetry Transport protocol version 3.1 and 3.1.1 MQTT provides a lightweight method of carrying out messaging using a publish/subscribe model. This makes it suitable for &quot;machine to machine&quot; messaging such as with low power sensors or mobile devices such as phones, embedded computers or micro-controllers like the Arduino.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nIn versions 1.6 to 2.0.11 of Eclipse Mosquitto, an MQTT v5 client connecting with a large number of user-property properties could cause excessive CPU usage, leading to a loss of performance and possible denial of service.(CVE-2021-41039)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"mosquitto","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP1","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/mosquitto&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"1.6.15-5.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["mosquitto-debugsource-1.6.15-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm","mosquitto-devel-1.6.15-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm","mosquitto-1.6.15-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm","mosquitto-debuginfo-1.6.15-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm"],"src":["mosquitto-1.6.15-5.oe1.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["mosquitto-debuginfo-1.6.15-5.oe1.x86_64.rpm","mosquitto-devel-1.6.15-5.oe1.x86_64.rpm","mosquitto-debugsource-1.6.15-5.oe1.x86_64.rpm","mosquitto-1.6.15-5.oe1.x86_64.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2022-1498.json"}},{"package":{"name":"mosquitto","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP2","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/mosquitto&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"1.6.15-5.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["mosquitto-debugsource-1.6.15-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm","mosquitto-1.6.15-5.oe1.aarch64.rpm","mosquit